    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho māgho devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, the glorious god Māgha, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:1.3",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho māgho devaputto bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
          "en": "and addressed the Buddha in verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:2.1",
          "pli": "“Kiṃsu chetvā sukhaṃ seti, ",
          "en": "“When what is incinerated do you sleep at ease? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:2.2",
          "pli": "kiṃsu chetvā na socati; ",
          "en": "When what is incinerated is there no sorrow? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:2.3",
          "pli": "Kissassu ekadhammassa, ",
          "en": "What is the one thing "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:2.4",
          "pli": "vadhaṃ rocesi gotamā”ti. ",
          "en": "whose killing you approve?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:3.1",
          "pli": "“Kodhaṃ chetvā sukhaṃ seti, ",
          "en": "“When anger’s incinerated you sleep at ease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:3.2",
          "pli": "kodhaṃ chetvā na socati; ",
          "en": "When anger’s incinerated there is no sorrow. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:3.3",
          "pli": "Kodhassa visamūlassa, ",
          "en": "Vatrabhū, anger has a poisoned root, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:3.4",
          "pli": "madhuraggassa vatrabhū; ",
          "en": "and a honey tip. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:3.5",
          "pli": "Vadhaṃ ariyā pasaṃsanti, ",
          "en": "The noble ones praise the slaying of anger, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.3:3.6",
          "pli": "tañhi chetvā na socatī”ti. ",
          "en": "for when it’s incinerated there is no sorrow.”"
        }
      ],
